Steps to download macmodes package and install dependencies:

Prerequesites:
- git
- python3 
- make 
- cc
- c++ 
- gfortran

To check c, c++ and fortran compilers (from PETSc docs):

    printf '#include<stdio.h>\nint main(){printf("cc OK!\\n");}' > t.c && cc t.c && ./a.out && rm -f t.c a.out
    printf '#include<iostream>\nint main(){std::cout<<"c++ OK!"<<std::endl;}' > t.cpp && c++ t.cpp && ./a.out && rm -f t.cpp a.out
    printf 'program t\nprint"(a)","gfortran OK!"\nend program' > t.f90 && gfortran t.f90 && ./a.out && rm -f t.f90 a.out

1. Clone github repo and cd there

    git clone https://github.com/logansmith0312/macmodes
    cd macmodes 
    
2. Create virtual enviroment 

    python3 -m venv .venv

3. Build PETSc 

    3a. Clone source code:

         git clone -b release https://gitlab.com/petsc/petsc.git petsc 
    
    3b. Configure installation: from top of PETSc source tree do:

        python3 /path_to_macmodes/docs/reconfigure_petsc.py
        
        Alternatively, do:

        ./configure --download-cmake --download-fblaslapack --download-metis --download-mpich --download-mumps --download-parmetis --download-scalapack --download-superlu_dist --with-scalar-type=complex
  

    3c. Follow prompts to compile and check installation 

    3d. Ensure enviroment variables PETSC_DIR and PETSC_ARCH are set, can add 
        them to .bashrc/.zshrc files, and prepend petsc bin to path:

        (bash)
        export PETSC_DIR='/path_to_petsc_dir'
        export PETSC_ARCH='architecture_name'

4. Build SLEPc

    4a. Clone source code:

        git clone -b release https://gitlab.com/slepc/slepc 

    4b. Ensure enviroment variable SLEPC_DIR is set
        
        (bash)
        export SLEPC_DIR='/path_to_slepc_dir'

    4c. Configure installation: from top of SLEPc source tree do:

        python3 /path_to_macmodes/docs/reconfigure_slepc.py

        Alternatively, do:

        ./configure 

    4d. Follow prompts to compile and check installation 

5. Install petsc4py from PETSc source tree

    5a. Navigate to macmodes directory, and activate virtual enviroment:

        source .venv/bin/activate

    5b. Install numpy:

        python3 -m pip install numpy

    5c. Install petsc4py (before check that $PETSC_DIR, $PETSC_ARCH are set):

        cd $PETSC_DIR
        python3 -m pip install src/binding/petsc4py


6. Install slepc4py from SLEPc source tree (before check that $PETSC_DIR, 
   $PETSC_ARCH, $SLEPC_DIR are set)

    cd $SLEPC_DIR
    python3 -m pip install src/binding/slepc4py

7. Install mpi4py

    7a. Ensure this is built on PETSc's own installation of MPICH, set:
        
        (bash)
        export MPICC=$PETSC_DIR/$PETSC_ARCH/bin/mpicc
        
    7b. Then install:

        python3 -m pip install mpi4py

    7c. Prepend petsc's bin to path (so you can call mpiexec and it defaults to
        petsc's own installation):

        (bash)
        export PATH="$PETSC_DIR/$PETSC_ARCH/bin:$PATH"

8. Install remaining dependencies and macmodes package itself:

    cd /path_to_macmodes/
    python3 -m pip install -e .

Documentation:
PETSc: https://petsc.org/release/install/download/
SLEPc: https://slepc.upv.es/release/installation/download.html 
petsc4py: https://petsc.org/release/petsc4py/install.html#
slepc4py: https://slepc.upv.es/release/slepc4py/install.html#

